<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="994" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[812,1420,1162,1420]" pageId="9" pageNumber="994">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,971,1162,1186]" pageId="9" pageNumber="994">Identification.</emphasis>
Our material of this species was identified based on the males, because females can be confused with other species, especially when in the macropterous form. All males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="White" authorityYear="1879" box="[1029,1148,1262,1286]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Microvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="994" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimula">
<emphasis box="[1029,1148,1262,1286]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="994">M. mimula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have the terminalia distinctly modified, with the dorsum of abdominal segment VIII expanded laterally, the venter of this segment widely excavated on the posterior margin, and the proctiger with large lateral projections (
<bibRefCitation author="Drake CJ &amp; Carvalho JCM" box="[1077,1358,1396,1420]" pageId="9" pageNumber="994" pagination="223 - 226" refId="ref15267" refString="Drake CJ, Carvalho JCM (1954) New waterstriders from Brazil (Hemiptera). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 67: 223 - 226." type="journal article" year="1954">Drake and Carvalho 1954</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
